The paper deals with action recognition using skeleton joints, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed model is a deep LSTM network, which involves learning feature representations and modeling temporal dependencies, indicating that it could also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions experimental results on human action recognition datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed dropout algorithm involves modifying the behavior of LSTM neurons, which could be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
